# Signs of the End Times: A Biblical and Current Events Analysis

---

## 1. Introduction

### Purpose

This study examines key biblical signs of the end times in light of current global events, using Scripture alone as our interpretive framework. The Bible interprets the Bible—we allow God's Word to define its own terms, establish its own patterns, and reveal its own meaning through the witness of multiple passages.

As Jesus commanded: *"Search the Scriptures; for in them ye think ye have eternal life: and they are they which testify of me"* (John 5:39). And as Isaiah declared: *"To the law and to the testimony: if they speak not according to this word, it is because there is no light in them"* (Isaiah 8:20).

### Overview of the Biblical Understanding of the Last Days

Scripture defines the "last days" as a period that began with Christ's first coming. The writer of Hebrews states: *"God, who at sundry times and in divers manners spake in time past unto the fathers by the prophets, hath in these last days spoken unto us by his Son"* (Hebrews 1:1-2). Peter, on the day of Pentecost, declared that the outpouring of the Spirit fulfilled Joel's prophecy concerning the last days (Acts 2:16-17, quoting Joel 2:28-32).

The apostle John confirmed this understanding: *"Little children, it is the last time: and as ye have heard that antichrist shall come, even now are there many antichrists; whereby we know that it is the last time"* (1 John 2:18).

Yet Scripture also reveals that the last days will intensify toward a climax. Paul wrote to Timothy: *"This know also, that in the last days perilous times shall come"* (2 Timothy 3:1). Jesus Himself provided specific signs to watch for, comparing them to birth pains that increase in frequency and intensity: *"All these are the beginning of sorrows"* (Matthew 24:8)—the Greek word "sorrows" (ōdin) means birth pangs.

The principle of convergence appears in Christ's teaching: *"So likewise ye, when ye shall see all these things, know that it is near, even at the doors"* (Matthew 24:33). Individual signs have appeared throughout the church age, but the simultaneous convergence of multiple signs marks the approach of the end.

